entries.femaleVariant: You replace your eyes, yet know not how to see.
You replace your legs, yet have nowhere to run.
You replace your hearts, yet you feel nothing.
You've come to believe in coin as the ultimate solution to any problem.
But the void within you billions of eurodollars could not fill. Good folk, this is not the path.
Succumb not to the baseness of flesh. Abandon the superficial and delve into your minds. Converse. Love one another.
The one opposite is not your foe but a wellspring of joy. The one beside you completes you.
To engage with him, with her, is to be happy. For happy are we who have the good fortune to care for another.
